subSubSection.paragraph:
Adult (
Figure 8D
): Wingspan 12.5–16.0 mm. This species is characterized by the yellowish-brown forewing with rounded brown spots at middle and near end of cell as well as at three-fifths length of fold, and the spots margined with yellowish-white; the eighth tergite roughly triangular, anterior margin heavily sclerotized, broadly concave in an arch, posterior margin rounded (
Figure 10H
), the lobes of vinculum sharp lateroapically, and the sacculus slightly narrowed gradually to apex in the male genitalia (
Figure 12C
); the corpus bursae irregularly oval-shaped, and the signum absent in the female genitalia (
Figure 14F
).
